HEMORRHAGIC FEVER WITH RENAL SYNDROME - RUSSIA (07): TATARSTAN
**************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

Date: Sat 27 Sep 2008
Source: Tatar 1 Inform News Agency online [in Russian, trans. Corr.BA, edited]
<http://www.tatar-inform.ru/news/2008/09/27/134262/>


During the period 19-25 Sep 2008 a total of 29 confirmed [or]
suspected cases of hemorrhagic fever with renal syndrome (HFRS) were
recorded in Tatarstan: 10 in Kazan, 8 in Naberezhnye Chelny, 3 in
Nizhnekamskiy area, 3 in Almetievskiy area, 2 in Sabinskiy area, 1 in
Kukmorskiy area, 1 in Leninogorskiy area, and 1 in Bavlinskiy area.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-RUS
<promed@promedmail.org>

[An unfavorable epidemic situation with regard to HFRS infection is
developing in Tatarstan. HFRS incidence in 2008 is almost 7 times more
than in 2007. In 2008 more than 100 HFRS cases have been recorded so
far, one with fatal outcome; 90 percent of cases occurred in
June-August, 11 percent of cases were registered in Kazan [the capital].
- Corr.BA

For more details concerning the epidemiology of HFRS in the Republic
of Tatarstan and adjacent regions the interested reader should
consult the commentary provided by Professor Henttonen in ProMED-mail
post entitled "Hemorrhagic fever w/renal synd - Russia (05):
(Tatarstan, Udmurtia)", archive number 20080730.2337.

The Tatarstan Republic can be located using the interactive map of
Russia available at
<http://map.rin.ru/index_e.html>. - Mod.CP
The areas where cases have been identified can be located on the
HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map at
<http://healthmap.org/promed?g=484048&v=55.333,51,5>. - CopyEd.MJ]
